All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    Chunk
    A document "chunk".
    CodeChunk
    A chunk containing code to be run.
    CommandRunner
    Run commands via the shell.
    DocChunk
    A chunk containing normal document content.
    ExecutionException
    Exception thrown when execution of shell commands fails.
    IProcessor
    Interface for an abstract "Processor", capable of taking a list of chunks, and "weaving" them into an output document that is emitted to a "destination" (a PrintStream).
    JDocGen  
    MemIO
    Holds a public PrintStream which can be written to in-memory; once finished, the written content can be retrieved with getContents.
    Parser
    Parses an input document into "chunks".
    Processor
    An abstract class implementing some behaviour for the IProcessor interface.
    ReverseProcessor
    A "do-nothing" sub-class of Processor, intended for use in testing.
    ShellProcessor
    A sub-class of Processor which makes use of the CommandRunner class to run the commands found in code chunks.
    StringUtilities
    Utility methods operating on strings.
